,{"contentful_id":"6ActoCh8yjdui2YuGPQcj9","title":"Redux","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"The world's most favourite React state management tool, which is pretty cool."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/7m94g1l1Ug1bM5KK4mwvhu/1b7aa54a0f80713e16174ef2227ecf04/5848309bcef1014c0b5e4a9a.png"},"title":"redux"},"link":{"contentful_id":"1n5bK0S9AYUahIk3dhwaft","title":"Redux","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"Redux - External Link","url":"https://redux.js.org/introduction/getting-started"}}},{"contentful_id":"6etbLqTFQGOfO66OAEuE0c","title":"Mobx","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"Mobx is that little kid on the block that suddenly fell into the limelight. Based on OOPS design, its slowly becoming the choice for anyone building simple apps with less complex state management needs. "},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/7lZ5fK7UgV10aQxLeGIVyo/0e7362f41959da403c7f63bd0460bc17/mobx.png"},"title":"mobx"},"link":{"contentful_id":"56HrHlAfRyyKWMq6Ifm6oT","title":"Mobx","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"Mobx - External Link","url":"https://mobx.js.org/README.html"}}},{"contentful_id":"2PwLmhCyTLWuC8a2YFoyVE","title":"Node","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"Knowing Node is imperative as its currently the go-to Javascript Runtime to build Webapps and REST APIs. Well, until Deno takes over, right?"},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/6HtB7rK0EMDjtysrOnEtmE/87c2d3c2ac0defaa277bfbb6639e80d4/1_tfZa4vsI6UusJYt_fzvGnQ.png"},"title":"Node"},"link":{"contentful_id":"3KPUU9HvPkj16TuqI1mYGS","title":"Node","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"Node - External Link","url":"https://nodejs.org/en/about/"}}},{"contentful_id":"QmUlcECkpJ5J6ANef0Zpr","title":"Gatsby","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"Gatsby is a blazing fast static site generator that employs React's Server-Side Rendering prowess to generate static HTML. And yes, this site has been built using this awesome framework."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/1Ef981ONoV4DRMrSopboyn/c4330bb61abd5a77577074998571ffad/gatsby-logo.png"},"title":"gatsby logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"1lcnSFNiDRdrWHSfUhFicj","title":"Gatsby","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"Gatsby - External Link","url":"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/docs/"}}},{"contentful_id":"4zJdkM8C8sk3jqeE81Ng6V","title":"Next","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"Whenever we hear Server-Side Rendering with React, Next.js comes to our mind. And it should, because its the most popular SSR framework built on React. Its biggest strength is providing the option of having both SSR and Static site generation, depending on use case. And yes, I love it!"},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/3oNFBO435yJS2uu2Dv0VZh/b39e0086685e165c2637166a157211a2/7axxa77t1lfrfz5keye1.png"},"title":"nextjs logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"BdIiCdcBiV8XDURbAQotI","title":"Next.js","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"Next - External Link","url":"https://nextjs.org/docs/getting-started"}}},{"contentful_id":"4yzMzOTH3ZuyZ50tq8FntU","title":"CSS3","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"You can't call yourself a front-end web developer if you don't know how to style your components. And I know my way around it and I would say I am average. Well, nobody starts as an expert, right?"},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/4MH8PIh0K1QGQZbEDAaId7/3e8dcbce8580764c5fce75e75736adc1/logo-2582747_960_720.png"},"title":"css3 logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"2VbUPem5Qydys6TiJlIvsh","title":"CSS3","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - CSS3","url":"https://www.w3.org/TR/2001/WD-css3-roadmap-20010523/"}}},{"contentful_id":"28Gwsng6IZqeFLUWiFHo7d","title":"TailwindCSS","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"This utility based CSS framework is my absolute favorite as it helps me build responsive components by generating classes based on my configuration. Hence, I like it more that Bootstrap."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/5FWDx8KaNgZsQFWISz6T9D/2c17657d64def0f3fcb262d955f52b21/Microsoft.VisualStudio.Services.Icons.Default"},"title":"TailwindCSS"},"link":{"contentful_id":"4GNqstnSsrSPUr8mVRZkFq","title":"TailwindCSS","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - TailwindCSS","url":"https://tailwindcss.com/"}}},{"contentful_id":"1DNJn1S0RsP1J2VfciBNfY","title":"SASS","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"I do prefer writing vanilla CSS when I am using a CSS framework, but if I need to write styles from scratch, I would surely use SCSS. Its just easier to target, manage and implement styles with SCSS. Pretty SASSy, huh?"},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/6tY7muMeVyTkYZnIjTsoEW/b496a41e8a361816e9be6d13c53e1c30/seal-color-aef0354c.png"},"title":"SASS"},"link":{"contentful_id":"4RS81dDsAWS2bm3On9OGaX","title":"SASS","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - SASS","url":"https://sass-lang.com/"}}},{"contentful_id":"5dTKuLw0JFnGd7pLSKZWWc","title":"GraphQL","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"GraphQL is to go-to query language for any developer trying to build Apps based on a NoSQL database. And its pretty cool that some frameworks like Gatsby brings it out of the box for managing its data. "},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/48ZWV3twOQmsmGHcjgNbQA/f6f37b468debb45cbbbd78ac1c562e5b/graphql.png"},"title":"graphql logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"4iiPkFhS6izIoJMLM0c73Y","title":"GraphQL","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - GraphQL","url":"https://graphql.org/"}}},{"contentful_id":"7smgYgFvg785Z1l0HZf9gX","title":"Contentful","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"I love working on websites built on Headless CMSes. Its really easy to manage and scale your content when your website doesn't have too many dynamic or user specific content. And Contentful is one of the major leaders in the Headless CMS community. Hence, I used it to build this app."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/3GRNVVv2bkjZHCpI7LHOIt/81437bf5f54404f9176ab150d754098a/347873-Mark_Circular_white_no_shadow-3d0a86-medium-1582585736.png"},"title":"contentful logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"5E4vXtBzFYjEnH4YU1Yjs4","title":"Contentful","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - Contentful","url":"https://www.contentful.com/"}}},{"contentful_id":"4LtUlNueVv1yq935g5Rp1M","title":"MongoDB","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"When I started out with web development, I had to rely on MongoDB for my data storage needs. And ever since I started an affair with CMSes, MongoDB has taken a backseat. But from time to time, I build microservices for which I use this amazing NoSQL DB to store my data. "},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/6QqBWcfc5AtcEEJuJg3kC7/9efa3e5c1a6ec5b913f122f5adaca205/logo-mongodb-png-mongodb-logo-png-400.png"},"title":"mongodb logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"Y4a07l1WpWqqEkhB8eZca","title":"MongoDB","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - MongoDB","url":"https://www.mongodb.com/"}}},{"contentful_id":"2spoqw6S8UF6yQlj2paF2Z","title":"Express","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"You can't call yourself a MEAN stack developer if you don't know Express. Its this lightweight framework that helps you write your RESTful APIs with ease. And coupled with its vast number plugins, it becomes a very formidable framework to create microservices."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/44X5U3c3Mvq4uTTKyNTtBV/f6d8509695a8e4129a0030afb56ba210/express.png"},"title":"express logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"1zbY1d7ZlYpDf6Q3g1Afr0","title":"Express","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - Express","url":"https://expressjs.com/"}}},{"contentful_id":"TIb0jlpIPL33Xtc3EpSkf","title":"Loopback","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"When it comes to writing microservices, Loopback comes to my mind first. Its a very robust framework with a lot of in-built enhancements that makes development a lot easier. However, I am more familiar with v3 and am still learning v4 as it has a huge number of new changes that reminds me of the transition from Angular v1.x to v2."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/6p4BRUz8NL3rJTIoJkawGq/508eb3a70b9621c129d219735f54a67b/loopback-4-logo-sample.png"},"title":"loopback logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"3Y6TaQx6eKZI48nlgtKISq","title":"Loopback.io","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - Loopback","url":"https://loopback.io/"}}},{"contentful_id":"2MDIcM61wz6OZM2g6d75JP","title":"Swiftype","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"I'll be honest, I don't know much about elastic search. But I do love how these third-party search providers help us with searching/filtering of content present in static sites or even all types of sites for that matter. I have worked on the site-search version of Swiftype for more than 1 year and I quite like it."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/E47J08KqQDKPy1BeuPTvD/d7221dab5026328ef5a58c54bb20472a/swiftype-logo-png-transparent.png"},"title":"swiftype logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"4s4NEDgn1xt7C1wmUUpeA7","title":"Swiftype","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - Swiftype","url":"https://swiftype.com/site-search"}}},{"contentful_id":"4mnBqX9JWYAWyOpU19M7pm","title":"Azure DevOps","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"Azure DevOps is an all-rounder when it comes to managing work items, repositories, build & release pipelines and many more. I am quite fond of it as it has taught me that building and managing a project can be very simple if all the things are present in one. And yes, I create and manage the build pipelines myself, as should any web developer."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/P3J0J1DcMtpIbGsGqqUyg/f45f617f00c5f9061626ece09386eaa1/Azure_20DevOps.png"},"title":"Azure devops logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"6oi93QjGPqE59kYJkjA5DB","title":"Azure DevOps","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - Azure DevOps","url":"https://azure.microsoft.com/en-in/services/devops/"}}},{"contentful_id":"1Wjfs5vkiBdbUFRSR8mR0q","title":"Azure","shortDescription":{"shortDescription":"Well, I know the basics of creating and managing webapps. Anything more than that, I would probably have to read that beautiful Microsoft documentation on Azure. And I have a rudimentary idea on how a Cloud Architecture should look like. As I said, I am a noob but a knowledge-hungry noob."},"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/rVANutUIoY5ByfNZcrkCN/90a399db35c774fdb4ffea920dd960b9/azure-1.png"},"title":"azure logo"},"link":{"contentful_id":"5TIHKs5QxCYcM7FOru4l0V","title":"Azure","variant":"Default","text":"Learn more","link":{"title":"External Link - Azure","url":"https://azure.microsoft.com/en-in/"}}}]},{"componentType":"ContentfulTypography","component":"h2","variant":"SectionHeading","body":{"body":"Want to get in touch?"}},{"componentType":"ContentfulSocialMediaSection","name":"Social Media Links","contentful_id":"MNk6MIvd6WtnL6VlyFF8x","socialCards":[{"contentful_id":"7w9tSQxwVS5e9BqW3PbkJS","title":"LinkedIn","shortDescription":null,"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/162102b9ma2k/xmes5timw53c03LGhdioF/fc03ff1c473a477964cd99cd928d2207/linkedIn.png"},"title":"linkedIn"},"link":{"contentful_id":"Y4GTX8Uo6FJtSmzHALMX2","title":"LinkedIn","variant":"Default","text":"LinkedIn","link":{"title":"LinkedIn - Profile Link","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/reetam-chatterjee-605637a8"}}},{"contentful_id":"2fiwGZZftMSjiFOAgbHang","title":"Facebook","shortDescription":null,"image":{"file":{"url":"//images.ctfass